            locale: 'en-us',
            uid: 'blt5ecf4981a7b5823c',
            _in_progress: false,
            body: '<p><span style="color: black;"><em>By Amy Thompson, EVP and Chief People Officer, Mattel</em></span><span style="color: black;"> –&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style="color: black;">At Mattel, our purpose is to empower the next generation to explore the wonder of childhood and reach their full potential. The incredible work of our employees is central to achieving this purpose – from the positive culture they create to the innovative ideas they bring forward.</span></p><p><span style="color: black;"></span><span style="color: black;">This is why we are thrilled to share that for the second year in a row, Mattel was </span><span style="color: black;"><strong>Certified™ by Great Place to Work</strong></span><span style="color: black;"><strong>®</strong> and recognized as one of </span><span style="color: black;"><strong>Fast Company’s 100 Best Workplaces for Innovators.</strong></span><span style="color: black;"><u></u></span></p><p><span style="color: black;"><strong>Great Place to Work</strong></span></p><p><span style="color: black;">Great Place to Work Certification is the global benchmark for identifying and recognizing outstanding employee experience. It is the only recognition based entirely on what employees report about their workplace experience – specifically, how consistently they experience a high-trust workplace.</span><span style="color: black;"></span></p><p><span style="color: black;">We are proud to share that 88%&nbsp;of&nbsp;our employees said Mattel is a a great place to work,&nbsp;compared to 57% of employees at a typical U.S. based company.</span></p><p><span style="color: black;">At Mattel, we are at our best when every member of our team feels respected, included and heard – when everyone can show up as themselves and do their best work. Our entire team plays a role in this. Thank you to our employees for fostering a culture of belonging and creating an environment where we all can thrive.</span><span style="color: black;"></span></p><p><span style="color: black;">You can learn more about what our employees have&nbsp;to say about Mattel&nbsp;</span><a href="https://www.greatplacetowork.com/certified-company/1000973" target="_blank">here</a><span style="color: black;"><em>.</em></span></p><p><span style="color: black;"><strong>Fast Company’s 100 Best Workplaces for Innovators</strong></span></p><p><span style="color: black;">This year’s recognition, developed by Fast Company in collaboration with Accenture, honors organizations and businesses across a variety of industries that demonstrate a steadfast commitment to encouraging innovation at all levels.</span></p><p><span style="color: black;">Innovation at every level has been a hallmark of Mattel since its founding, and we strongly believe that a good idea can come from anyone, anywhere. No matter where you work in the organization, you can always make a difference and have real impact. We welcome fresh ideas and value new initiatives that challenge conventional thinking.</span></p><p><span style="color: black;">We’re excited to share that this year Mattel ranked No. 23 on </span><a href="https://www.fastcompany.com/best-workplaces-for-innovators/list" target="_blank">Fast Company’s 100 Best Workplaces for Innovators</a><span style="color: black;"> list for continuing to drive growth and innovation throughout the organization – from our products and experiences to our people.</span></p><p><span style="color: black;">We are so honored to receive these recognitions from Great Place to Work and Fast Company once again this year. They are a meaningful reflection of our workplace culture and the achievements of our entire organization.</span></p><p><span style="color: black;">Congratulations to everyone at Mattel!</span></p>',
